The Kano State Government has announced that one coronavirus death has been recorded in the State. The State’s Ministry of Health disclosed this in a tweet via its Twitter account on Thursday. The Ministry also announced that 41 additional patients have been discharged following full recovery from the virus. According to the Ministry, ten new cases of the disease were also recorded in the State. The tweet reads “Update as at 11:47pm 4th May 2020. “135 samples of COVID19 were tested today in Kano. “10 new cases of COVID19 in Kano confirmed. “41 additional COVID19Kano patients were discharged. “Sadly, 1 COVID19Kano death was also recorded today. “Residents are advised to stay safe and always mask up.” These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More